# 4. LEVEL-WISE ARRAY QUESTIONS

---

# LEVEL 1 — EASY FOUNDATION

Goal:
Build confidence and implementation skills.

---

# Pattern 1 — Basic Traversal

Questions:

* Largest Element
* Smallest Element
* Second Largest
* Check Sorted Array
* Reverse Array
* Sum of Array
* Average of Array
* Count Even/Odd
* Find Missing Number
* Find Frequency
* Find Maximum Difference

Skills learned:

* loops,
* conditions,
* variable tracking.

---

# Pattern 2 — Searching

Questions:

* Linear Search
* Binary Search
* Lower Bound
* Upper Bound
* First Occurrence
* Last Occurrence
* Count Occurrences

Skills:

* searching logic,
* sorted array thinking.

---

# Pattern 3 — Sorting Basics

Questions:

* Bubble Sort
* Selection Sort
* Insertion Sort

Goal:
Understand sorting mechanics deeply.

---

# Pattern 4 — Two Pointers Easy

Questions:

* Reverse Array
* Remove Duplicates
* Move Zeros to End
* Merge Two Sorted Arrays
* Two Sum (sorted)
* Valid Palindrome

Recognition:
Usually sorted arrays or opposite movement.

---

# Pattern 5 — Hashing Easy

Questions:

* Two Sum
* Contains Duplicate
* Majority Element
* Find Unique Element
* Frequency Count

Skills:

* HashMap,
* HashSet,
* frequency thinking.

---

# Pattern 6 — Sliding Window Easy

Questions:

* Maximum Sum Subarray of Size K
* Average of Subarrays
* First Negative Number in Window
* Count Distinct in Window

Recognition:
Fixed-size contiguous window.

---

# Pattern 7 — Matrix Basics

Questions:

* Matrix Traversal
* Row Sum
* Column Sum
* Transpose Matrix
* Rotate Matrix 90°
* Spiral Traversal

---

# LEVEL 2 — MEDIUM (MOST IMPORTANT)

This is the real interview level.

Goal:
Pattern recognition + optimization.

---

# Pattern 8 — Advanced Two Pointers

Questions:

* 3Sum
* Container With Most Water
* Trapping Rain Water
* Dutch National Flag
* Sort Colors
* Pair Difference
* Remove Duplicates II

Key thinking:
Pointer movement should eliminate unnecessary checks.

---

# Pattern 9 — Advanced Sliding Window

Questions:

* Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters
* Maximum Consecutive Ones
* Fruits Into Baskets
* Longest Repeating Character Replacement
* Minimum Size Subarray Sum
* Permutation in String

Key insight:
Dynamic window expansion/shrinking.

---

# Pattern 10 — Prefix Sum

Questions:

* Subarray Sum Equals K
* Range Sum Query
* Pivot Index
* Continuous Subarray Sum
* Product Except Self
* Equilibrium Index

Key thinking:
Store previous computations.

---

# Pattern 11 — Kadane’s Algorithm

Questions:

* Maximum Subarray
* Maximum Product Subarray
* Circular Subarray Sum

Critical insight:
Discard negative contribution.

---

# Pattern 12 — Binary Search Medium

Questions:

* Search in Rotated Sorted Array
* Find Peak Element
* Single Element in Sorted Array
* Find Minimum in Rotated Array
* Median of Two Sorted Arrays

Skills:

* divide and conquer,
* monotonic properties.

---

# Pattern 13 — Greedy Arrays

Questions:

* Jump Game
* Jump Game II
* Gas Station
* Candy Distribution

Key thinking:
Local optimal → global optimal.

---

# Pattern 14 — Cyclic Sort Pattern

Questions:

* Missing Number
* Find Duplicate
* First Missing Positive
* Set Mismatch

Recognition:
Array values related to indices.

---

# Pattern 15 — Monotonic Stack + Arrays

Questions:

* Next Greater Element
* Daily Temperatures
* Largest Rectangle in Histogram
* Stock Span

Recognition:
Nearest greater/smaller element problems.

---

