# 9. Final Advice

Array mastery is NOT about:

* solving 1000 questions.

It is about:

* recognizing structures,
* identifying patterns,
* optimizing logically,
* thinking clearly under pressure.

If you deeply master:

* Two Pointers,
* Sliding Window,
* Prefix Sum,
* Hashing,
* Binary Search,

you can solve MOST medium interview questions confidently.

Consistency matters more than intensity.
Solve daily.
Re-solve frequently.
Think deeply.
